global clients */
const db_name = 'nunl-settings';
const db_version = 1; // should be int
const db_store_name = 'settings';
const db_device_secret_key = 'spns_device_secret';

const spns_request_id_key = 'SPNS-Request-Id';

/**
 * Open indexedDB with name and upgrade callback.
 * @param {string} name Database name.
 * @param {number} version Specify databse version. Should be integer.
 * @param {callback} upgradeCallback Completion which will be called
 *     if upgrade is required.
 * @return {Promise<indexeddb|error>} Promise object represents the databse.
 */
function openDatabase (name, version, upgradeCallback) {
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) =&gt; {
        var request = indexedDB.open(name, version);
        request.onsuccess = function (e) {
            var db = e.target.result;
            resolve(db);
        };
        request.onerror = function (event) {
            reject(event.target.errorCode);
        };
        request.onupgradeneeded = function (event) {
            var db = event.target.result;
            upgradeCallback(db);
        };
    });
};

/**
 * Short hand for settings database.
 * @return {Promise<indexeddb|error>} Promise object represents the settings database.
 */
function settings () {
    return openDatabase(db_name, db_version, (upgrade_db) =&gt; {
        if (!upgrade_db.objectStoreNames.contains(db_store_name)) {
            upgrade_db.createObjectStore(db_store_name, { keyPath: 'key' });
        }
    });
}

/**
 * Set value in settings for a given key.
 * @param {string} key Key in settings.
 * @param {string} value Value to store.
 * @return {Promise<indexeddb|error>} Promise object represents the database.
 */
function set_value_for_key (key, value) {
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) =&gt; {
        settings().then(function (db) {
            var request = db.transaction(['settings'], 'readwrite')
                .objectStore(db_store_name)
                .put({ key: key, value: value });
            request.onsuccess = function (e) {
                console.log('[ServiceWorker] did set value: "' + value +
                    '", for key: "' + key + '"');
                resolve(db);
            };
            request.onerror = function (event) {
                console.log('[ServiceWorker] failed to set value: "' + value +
                    '", for key: "' + key + '"');
                reject(event.target.errorCode);
            };
        });
    });
}

/**
 * Get value from settings for a given key.
 * @param {string} key Key in settings.
 * @return {Promise<string|error>} Promise object respesents the value.
 */
function get_value_for_key (key) {
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) =&gt; {
        settings().then(function (db) {
            var request = db.transaction('settings', 'readonly')
                .objectStore(db_store_name)
                .get(key);
            request.onsuccess = function (event) {
                resolve(event.target.result.value);
            };
            request.onerror = function (event) {
                reject(event.target.errorCode);
            };
        });
    });
}

/**
 * Helper function to check if value is string.
 * @param {*} value Value to check type of.
 */
function isString (value) {
    // A string is 'string' except if created with new String
    // typeof will return "object"
    return typeof value === 'string' || value instanceof String;
}

/**
 * Sends analytics to SPNS. Implemented in place to remove dependency
 * to SPNS SDK.
 * @param {string} secret Secret received from SPNS SDK at in message.
 * @param {string} request_id Identifier of the current push messages.
 * @param {string} status Can be 'received' or 'opened'.
 * @return {Promise} Completion promise.
 */
function report_push (secret, request_id, status) {
    const url_components = [
        'https://spns-ping.sanomamdc.com/api/delivery',
        secret,
        request_id,
        status
    ];
    return fetch(url_components.join('/'));
}

/**
 * Handles `intall` event which is sent once at worker get start
 * execution for the first time.
 */
self.addEventListener('install', function (event) {
    console.log('[ServiceWorker] install');
    self.skipWaiting();
});

/**
 * Handles custome message post from the client or another worker.
 * Currently SPNS SDK sends device secret at sucessfull registration.
 */
self.addEventListener('message', function (event) {
    // Some events like 'keyChanged' from Firebase provide object
    // in data field.
    if (!isString(event.data)) {
        return;
    }

    try {
        var data = JSON.parse(event.data);
        // SPNS doesn't provide message type. Trying to workaround it we
        // will check if required property exists.
        if ('deviceSecret' in data) {
            console.log('[ServiceWorker] message: "' + data.deviceSecret + '"');
            var setSecretPromise = set_value_for_key(db_device_secret_key, data.deviceSecret);
            event.waitUntil(setSecretPromise);
        }
    } catch (e) {}
});

/**
 * Handles a new push message.
 */
self.addEventListener('push', function (event) {
    var options = event.data.json();

    var analyticsPromise = get_value_for_key(db_device_secret_key).then(function (secret) {
        // Reporting back to SPNS that push was received
        const request_id = options.data[spns_request_id_key];
        return report_push(secret, request_id, 'received');
    });

    var title = options.title;
    var notificationPromise = self.registration.showNotification(title, options);
    var promiseChain = Promise.all([
        analyticsPromise,
        notificationPromise
    ]);
    event.waitUntil(promiseChain);
});

/**
 * Handles a click on a system notification message.
 */
self.addEventListener('notificationclick', function (event) {
    event.notification.close();

    var options = event.notification;
    const request_id = options.data[spns_request_id_key];

    var analyticsPromise = get_value_for_key(db_device_secret_key).then(function (secret) {
        // Reporting back to SPNS that push was oppened
        return report_push(secret, request_id, 'opened');
    });

    var type = options.data.type;
    var article_id = options.data.article_id;
    var url_components = [self.location.origin];
    if (type === 'article' &amp;&amp; article_id !== 'undefined') {
        url_components.push('artikel');
        url_components.push(article_id);
        url_components.push('redirect.html?push_request_id=' + request_id + '&amp;source=notification-open');
    }
    var url = url_components.join('/');

    var openPagePromise = clients.matchAll({
        type: 'window',
        includeUncontrolled: true // Include windows which are not controlled by this worker
    })
        .then(function (windowClients) {
            // Checking if there is window/tab with current url already open
            // and focus this one otherwise open a new window
            for (var i = 0; i &lt; windowClients.length; i++) {
                var client = windowClients[i];
                if (client.url === url &amp;&amp; 'focus' in client) {
                    return client.focus();
                }
            }
            if (clients.openWindow) {
                return clients.openWindow(url);
            }
        });

    var promiseChain = Promise.all([
        analyticsPromise,
        openPagePromise
    ]);
    event.waitUntil(promiseChain);
});

Daarnaast houden ze bij het\n      online winkelen je digitale winkelwagentje bij. Ook kunnen websitehouders dankzij cookies zien hoe vaak hun sites -\n      en welke paginas - door bezoekers worden bekeken (statistieken). "AIzaSyA6pECfxuliAVNFGf1vjhJ9YhuE4xQD4LI", "auth_domain": "nunl-e7a0d-4.firebaseapp.com"}, {"database_url": "https://nunl-e7a0d-5.firebaseio.com", "api_key": "AIzaSyA6pECfxuliAVNFGf1vjhJ9YhuE4xQD4LI", "auth_domain": "nunl-e7a0d-5.firebaseapp.com"}]}/* global clients */
const db_name = 'nunl-settings';
const db_version = 1; // should be int
const db_store_name = 'settings';
const db_device_secret_key = 'spns_device_secret';

const spns_request_id_key = 'SPNS-Request-Id';

/**
 * Open indexedDB with name and upgrade callback.
 * @param {string} name Database name.
 * @param {number} version Specify databse version. Should be integer.
 * @param {callback} upgradeCallback Completion which will be called
 *     if upgrade is required.
 * @return {Promise<indexeddb|error>} Promise object represents the databse.
 */
function openDatabase (name, version, upgradeCallback) {
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) =&gt; {
        var request = indexedDB.open(name, version);
        request.onsuccess = function (e) {
            var db = e.target.result;
            resolve(db);
        };
        request.onerror = function (event) {
            reject(event.target.errorCode);
        };
        request.onupgradeneeded = function (event) {
            var db = event.target.result;
            upgradeCallback(db);
        };
    });
};

/**
 * Short hand for settings database.
 * @return {Promise<indexeddb|error>} Promise object represents the settings database.
 */
function settings () {
    return openDatabase(db_name, db_version, (upgrade_db) =&gt; {
        if (!upgrade_db.objectStoreNames.contains(db_store_name)) {
            upgrade_db.createObjectStore(db_store_name, { keyPath: 'key' });
        }
    });
}

/**
 * Set value in settings for a given key.
 * @param {string} key Key in settings.
 * @param {string} value Value to store.
 * @return {Promise<indexeddb|error>} Promise object represents the database.
 */
function set_value_for_key (key, value) {
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) =&gt; {
        settings().then(function (db) {
            var request = db.transaction(['settings'], 'readwrite')
                .objectStore(db_store_name)
                .put({ key: key, value: value });
            request.onsuccess = function (e) {
                console.log('[ServiceWorker] did set value: "' + value +
                    '", for key: "' + key + '"');
                resolve(db);
            };
            request.onerror = function (event) {
                console.log('[ServiceWorker] failed to set value: "' + value +
                    '", for key: "' + key + '"');
                reject(event.target.errorCode);
            };
        });
    });
}

/**
 * Get value from settings for a given key.
 * @param {string} key Key in settings.
 * @return {Promise<string|error>} Promise object respesents the value.
 */
function get_value_for_key (key) {
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) =&gt; {
        settings().then(function (db) {
            var request = db.transaction('settings', 'readonly')
                .objectStore(db_store_name)
                .get(key);
            request.onsuccess = function (event) {
                resolve(event.target.result.value);
            };
            request.onerror = function (event) {
                reject(event.target.errorCode);
            };
        });
    });
}

/**
 * Helper function to check if value is string.
 * @param {*} value Value to check type of.
 */
function isString (value) {
    // A string is 'string' except if created with new String
    // typeof will return "object"
    return typeof value === 'string' || value instanceof String;
}

/**
 * Sends analytics to SPNS. Implemented in place to remove dependency
 * to SPNS SDK.
 * @param {string} secret Secret received from SPNS SDK at in message.
 * @param {string} request_id Identifier of the current push messages.
 * @param {string} status Can be 'received' or 'opened'.
 * @return {Promise} Completion promise.
 */
function report_push (secret, request_id, status) {
    const url_components = [
        'https://spns-ping.sanomamdc.com/api/delivery',
        secret,
        request_id,
        status
    ];
    return fetch(url_components.join('/'));
}

/**
 * Handles `intall` event which is sent once at worker get start
 * execution for the first time.
 */
self.addEventListener('install', function (event) {
    console.log('[ServiceWorker] install');
    self.skipWaiting();
});

/**
 * Handles custome message post from the client or another worker.
 * Currently SPNS SDK sends device secret at sucessfull registration.
 */
self.addEventListener('message', function (event) {
    // Some events like 'keyChanged' from Firebase provide object
    // in data field.
    if (!isString(event.data)) {
        return;
    }

    try {
        var data = JSON.parse(event.data);
        // SPNS doesn't provide message type. Trying to workaround it we
        // will check if required property exists.
        if ('deviceSecret' in data) {
            console.log('[ServiceWorker] message: "' + data.deviceSecret + '"');
            var setSecretPromise = set_value_for_key(db_device_secret_key, data.deviceSecret);
            event.waitUntil(setSecretPromise);
        }
    } catch (e) {}
});

/**
 * Handles a new push message.
 */
self.addEventListener('push', function (event) {
    var options = event.data.json();

    var analyticsPromise = get_value_for_key(db_device_secret_key).then(function (secret) {
        // Reporting back to SPNS that push was received
        const request_id = options.data[spns_request_id_key];
        return report_push(secret, request_id, 'received');
    });

    var title = options.title;
    var notificationPromise = self.registration.showNotification(title, options);
    var promiseChain = Promise.all([
        analyticsPromise,
        notificationPromise
    ]);
    event.waitUntil(promiseChain);
});

/**
 * Handles a click on a system notification message.
 */
self.addEventListener('notificationclick', function (event) {
    event.notification.close();

    var options = event.notification;
    const request_id = options.data[spns_request_id_key];

    var analyticsPromise = get_value_for_key(db_device_secret_key).then(function (secret) {
        // Reporting back to SPNS that push was oppened
        return report_push(secret, request_id, 'opened');
    });

    var type = options.data.type;
    var article_id = options.data.article_id;
    var url_components = [self.location.origin];
    if (type === 'article' &amp;&amp; article_id !== 'undefined') {
        url_components.push('artikel');
        url_components.push(article_id);
        url_components.push('redirect.html?push_request_id=' + request_id + '&amp;source=notification-open');
    }
    var url = url_components.join('/');

    var openPagePromise = clients.matchAll({
        type: 'window',
        includeUncontrolled: true // Include windows which are not controlled by this worker
    })
        .then(function (windowClients) {
            // Checking if there is window/tab with current url already open
            // and focus this one otherwise open a new window
            for (var i = 0; i &lt; windowClients.length; i++) {
                var client = windowClients[i];
                if (client.url === url &amp;&amp; 'focus' in client) {
                    return client.focus();
                }
            }
            if (clients.openWindow) {
                return clients.openWindow(url);
            }
        });

    var promiseChain = Promise.all([
        analyticsPromise,
        openPagePromise
    ]);
    event.waitUntil(promiseChain);
});

                    sanoma_account_global_config['api_key'] = '3_rlSSasCKaY6Id8VY1d13AO1IbHGsXzDrPIVha-Aup28W6guE9vkRb6whOO1Z2O67';
                }
                jQuery.cachedScript('https://account.sanomaservices.nl/js/sanoma_account.min.js');
        </script>

<div class="block headline section-nuzakelijk" data-id="block-411128" data-position="" data-sac-marker="block.headline" data-type="headline" id="block-411128">
<a class="block-title section-bgcolored" href="/economie">

const db_name = 'nunl-settings';
const db_version = 1; // should be int
const db_store_name = 'settings';
const db_device_secret_key = 'spns_device_secret';

const spns_request_id_key = 'SPNS-Request-Id';

/**
 * Open indexedDB with name and upgrade callback.
 * @param {string} name Database name.
 * @param {number} version Specify databse version. Should be integer.
 * @param {callback} upgradeCallback Completion which will be called
 *     if upgrade is required.
 * @return {Promise<indexeddb|error>} Promise object represents the databse.
 */
function openDatabase (name, version, upgradeCallback) {
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) =&gt; {
        var request = indexedDB.open(name, version);
        request.onsuccess = function (e) {
            var db = e.target.result;
            resolve(db);
        };
        request.onerror = function (event) {
            reject(event.target.errorCode);
        };
        request.onupgradeneeded = function (event) {
            var db = event.target.result;
            upgradeCallback(db);
        };
    });
};

/**
 * Short hand for settings database.
 * @return {Promise<indexeddb|error>} Promise object represents the settings database.
 */
function settings () {
    return openDatabase(db_name, db_version, (upgrade_db) =&gt; {
        if (!upgrade_db.objectStoreNames.contains(db_store_name)) {
            upgrade_db.createObjectStore(db_store_name, { keyPath: 'key' });
        }
    });
}

/**
 * Set value in settings for a given key.
 * @param {string} key Key in settings.
 * @param {string} value Value to store.
 * @return {Promise<indexeddb|error>} Promise object represents the database.
 */
function set_value_for_key (key, value) {
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) =&gt; {
        settings().then(function (db) {
            var request = db.transaction(['settings'], 'readwrite')
                .objectStore(db_store_name)
                .put({ key: key, value: value });
            request.onsuccess = function (e) {
                console.log('[ServiceWorker] did set value: "' + value +
                    '", for key: "' + key + '"');
                resolve(db);
            };
            request.onerror = function (event) {
                console.log('[ServiceWorker] failed to set value: "' + value +
                    '", for key: "' + key + '"');
                reject(event.target.errorCode);
            };
        });
    });
}

/**
 * Get value from settings for a given key.
 * @param {string} key Key in settings.
 * @return {Promise<string|error>} Promise object respesents the value.
 */
function get_value_for_key (key) {
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) =&gt; {
        settings().then(function (db) {
            var request = db.transaction('settings', 'readonly')
                .objectStore(db_store_name)
                .get(key);
            request.onsuccess = function (event) {
                resolve(event.target.result.value);
            };
            request.onerror = function (event) {
                reject(event.target.errorCode);
            };
        });
    });
}

/**
 * Helper function to check if value is string.
 * @param {*} value Value to check type of.
 */
function isString (value) {
    // A string is 'string' except if created with new String
    // typeof will return "object"
    return typeof value === 'string' || value instanceof String;
}

/**
 * Sends analytics to SPNS. Implemented in place to remove dependency
 * to SPNS SDK.
 * @param {string} secret Secret received from SPNS SDK at in message.
 * @param {string} request_id Identifier of the current push messages.
 * @param {string} status Can be 'received' or 'opened'.
 * @return {Promise} Completion promise.
 */
function report_push (secret, request_id, status) {
    const url_components = [
        'https://spns-ping.sanomamdc.com/api/delivery',
        secret,
        request_id,
        status
    ];
    return fetch(url_components.join('/'));
}

/**
 * Handles `intall` event which is sent once at worker get start
 * execution for the first time.
 */
self.addEventListener('install', function (event) {
    console.log('[ServiceWorker] install');
    self.skipWaiting();
});

/**
 * Handles custome message post from the client or another worker.
 * Currently SPNS SDK sends device secret at sucessfull registration.
 */
self.addEventListener('message', function (event) {
    // Some events like 'keyChanged' from Firebase provide object
    // in data field.
    if (!isString(event.data)) {
        return;
    }

    try {
        var data = JSON.parse(event.data);
        // SPNS doesn't provide message type. Trying to workaround it we
        // will check if required property exists.
        if ('deviceSecret' in data) {
            console.log('[ServiceWorker] message: "' + data.deviceSecret + '"');
            var setSecretPromise = set_value_for_key(db_device_secret_key, data.deviceSecret);
            event.waitUntil(setSecretPromise);
        }
    } catch (e) {}
});

/**
 * Handles a new push message.
 */
self.addEventListener('push', function (event) {
    var options = event.data.json();

    var analyticsPromise = get_value_for_key(db_device_secret_key).then(function (secret) {
        // Reporting back to SPNS that push was received
        const request_id = options.data[spns_request_id_key];
        return report_push(secret, request_id, 'received');
    });

    var title = options.title;
    var notificationPromise = self.registration.showNotification(title, options);
    var promiseChain = Promise.all([
        analyticsPromise,
        notificationPromise
    ]);
    event.waitUntil(promiseChain);
});

/**
 * Handles a click on a system notification message.
 */
self.addEventListener('notificationclick', function (event) {
    event.notification.close();

    var options = event.notification;
    const request_id = options.data[spns_request_id_key];

    var analyticsPromise = get_value_for_key(db_device_secret_key).then(function (secret) {
        // Reporting back to SPNS that push was oppened
        return report_push(secret, request_id, 'opened');
    });

    var type = options.data.type;
    var article_id = options.data.article_id;
    var url_components = [self.location.origin];
    if (type === 'article' &amp;&amp; article_id !== 'undefined') {
        url_components.push('artikel');
        url_components.push(article_id);
        url_components.push('redirect.html?push_request_id=' + request_id + '&amp;source=notification-open');
    }
    var url = url_components.join('/');

    var openPagePromise = clients.matchAll({
        type: 'window',
        includeUncontrolled: true // Include windows which are not controlled by this worker
    })
        .then(function (windowClients) {
            // Checking if there is window/tab with current url already open
            // and focus this one otherwise open a new window
            for (var i = 0; i &lt; windowClients.length; i++) {
                var client = windowClients[i];
                if (client.url === url &amp;&amp; 'focus' in client) {
                    return client.focus();
                }
            }
            if (clients.openWindow) {
                return clients.openWindow(url);
            }
        });

    var promiseChain = Promise.all([
        analyticsPromise,
        openPagePromise
    ]);
    event.waitUntil(promiseChain);
});
</string|error></indexeddb|error></indexeddb|error></indexeddb|error>
